# Walkthrough - Async Distributed ADMM (Paper Implementation)

I have implemented the **Delay-Aware Consensus ADMM** algorithm based on the paper "Asynchronous Distributed Multi-Robot Motion Planning Under Imperfect Communication".

## Implementation Details

### Core Logic: [async_admm_paper.py](file:///home/sriv/async_admm_paper.py)
- **Agent Class**: Implements local trajectory optimization using `scipy.optimize.minimize`.
    - **Adaptive Penalty**: $\rho_{ij} = \rho_{base} / (1 + d_{ij})$
    - **Formation Control**: Each agent $i$ tracks $x_i(t) \to z(t) + \text{offset}_i$.
- **AsyncSimulator Class**:
    - Simulates random communication delays ($d_{ij} \in [0, d_{max}]$).
    - **Global Consensus**: Computes virtual center $z$ by aggregating $x_i - \text{offset}_i$.

### Simulation Scenario: Stress Test
- **Scenario**: 6 Robots forming a **Hexagon Formation**.
- **Delays**: High delay environment (Max 8 steps, 90% probability).
- **Goal**: Maintain formation under chaotic communication.

